                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Leadership points are the most braindead, idiotic thing that Sony has come up with to date.  It isn't about the skills, they actually appear to be useful.  It is about how you earn experience.  Leadership experience isn't a slider like aa vs level exp, you get leadership experience when you are a group or raid leader for each kill that the group or raid makes.   That is stupid on several levels:
<br />

<br />
1.  It forces guilds to choose raid a single raid leader.   From what I have heard, acquiring raid experience is SLOW.  No guild is going to allow many people to acquire raid experience, because the abilities need to be maxed as soon as possible.  I don't even want to think about the hard feelings that are going to result from players that aren't the one guy that always gets raid leader experience.  Building successful MMORPG's means creating communities.  What idiot decided to create something that is guarenteed to be devisive?  Did they learn *nothing* when they were asked to put raid experience into the game in the first place?
<br />

<br />
2.  It prevents anyone that aspires to be a raid leader from becoming a raid leader.  Hello, you are new to the guild and are a good organizer?  Sorry, you will never be a raid leader because you have to lead in order to get the skills.  Why would any guild let you lead when our raid leader doesn't have the skills maxed?
<br />

<br />
3.  It puts an entire guild at the mercy of one player.  If that player leaves the game, the entire guild loses out.  People quit the game.  People quit the game more often when they are burned out and the game isn't fun anymore.  Gee, let's create a system that puts the onus on ONE person to always be there or the guild loses out.  Make it so they have to play all the time or let down 70 odd friends.
<br />

<br />
4.  This makes it really hard to be a hero.  This is a heroic fantasy game.  It is about character development.  In an environment where raids are 36 or 72 people, 1 guy gets to be the hero, and 35 or 71 get to be the also rans, not just on one raid, but on almost all of them.  Gee, great idea.  I have no way to earn this experience from my own efforts and sacrifice, I have to have 70 friends around that all want to spend their time developing my character....  Yeah, that is gonna happen.
<br />

<br />
5.  These are user interface and communications tools.  Why are they AA to begin with?  Did we pay aa for maps?  For /shout, for /te?  Why are we suddenly paying for the ability to communicate?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Oznoyng Castintank, Coercer of Inner Circle, Xegony
<br />
E65.223/Xg h-- 5272hp 6480mp ft25 G++++!! e++++ o++ T++ L H+++ f g !b c+++ t++++ D+</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
