                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree that the leadership point system, inasmuch as it has been revealed, is *completely retarded*.  I have no problem with people who have 40+ hours a week to play and raid, raid, raid getting better rewards than the people who have jobs and families and are threfore casual players.  (I guess.  Both kinds of players pay the same amount to Sony every month, but oh well.)
<br />

<br />
However, as far as I can tell, this "leadership system" will be divisive, very devisive--everyone wants to be valuable, and despite the last point I do think people will clamor to lead raids in order get special abilities or whatever.  Secondly, the system will further stratify the current two-tiered population of players in EQ: those with the time and inclination to join an uber guild and raid, raid, raid, and those who don't.  
<br />

<br />
Also, the idea of having an "guild owned" toon to lead raids would violate the EULA, so that's hardly an argument in Sony's favor.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646635" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saediien Iluvatri</a>
