                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Those of you in raiding guilds have issues to work out on leadership and who gets the experience... My last understanding was that SOE planned on implementing xp for group leaders as well..... Imagine... group leader A has a 5 man group .... player incoming needs and invite.....Member B says "make me leader a sec".... "NO WAY IM LDR!"...
<br />

<br />
This is a way to make pickup groups totally impossible ... you are going to have more people with the looking for more tags up than lfg..... and everyone is going to argue over leadership if the reward become useful...
<br />

<br />
The better the reward and the more restricted the chance to increase it and I see "leadership" becoming a sore point.  Most groups run on consensus... if youre not comfortable you leave....adding ego to the equation doesnt help for stable grouping.
<br />

<br />
Further, a lot of pickup players already advertise as wont group unless you have cleric, cc, etc... Will we have a bunch of people who wont group unless they get to be LDR? or Will we have players who wont join a group unless the LDR has certain abilities already?
<br />

<br />
This can make player relations a nightmare , especially if you group with people who are highly motivated or you are on the pickup group circuit.
<br />

<br />
Hope enough people leave for the new continent and I can work on soloing some of the more crowded zones to increase my content.....</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
